From: ETA project local patch
Subject: [PATCH] Direct-int notification dispatch — skip Variant wrap in C# bridge

Problem
-------
CSharpInstance::_call_notification (modules/mono/csharp_script.cpp:1958) is
called for every NOTIFICATION_PROCESS, NOTIFICATION_PHYSICS_PROCESS,
NOTIFICATION_INTERNAL_PHYSICS_PROCESS, NOTIFICATION_TRANSFORM_CHANGED, and
~40 other notifications on every C# script instance every frame.

The original implementation wraps the int notification value in a Variant
plus allocates a Variant for the return slot, then dispatches via the
generic CSharpInstanceBridge_Call path:

    Variant arg = p_notification;
    const Variant *args[1] = { &arg };
    Variant ret;
    Callable::CallError call_error;
    GDMonoCache::managed_callbacks.CSharpInstanceBridge_Call(
        gchandle.get_intptr(), &SNAME("_notification"),
        args, 1, &call_error, &ret);

That's 2 Variant constructions + the managed-side unboxing per dispatch.
At N C# nodes × ~5 notifications per node per physics tick × 128 Hz, this
adds up to >100k Variant ctor/dtor pairs per second from this site alone
on a populated round.

Fix
---
Add a dedicated managed callback CSharpInstanceBridge_CallNotification
that takes a raw int and dispatches to GodotObject._Notification(int)
directly. The source-generated InvokeGodotClassMethod path for
_notification on user scripts already routes to the same virtual
_Notification(int) override, so behaviour is preserved bit-for-bit;
only the Variant round-trip is removed.

The generic Call path stays in place untouched for every other method
invocation; this is purely additive on the binding surface.

Verified
--------
TODO — re-measure with bot-match scenario, populate ObjectDB-Profiler
oscillation delta + Gen0/1 GC count delta vs. baseline. Expected:
elimination of the steady-state Variant churn attributable to
_call_notification in the spike-log GC delta column.

Patch
-----

--- a/modules/mono/csharp_script.cpp
+++ b/modules/mono/csharp_script.cpp
@@ -1956,13 +1956,12 @@ void CSharpInstance::notification(int p_notification, bool p_reversed) {
 }

 void CSharpInstance::_call_notification(int p_notification, bool p_reversed) {
-	Variant arg = p_notification;
-	const Variant *args[1] = { &arg };
-
-	Variant ret;
-	Callable::CallError call_error;
-	GDMonoCache::managed_callbacks.CSharpInstanceBridge_Call(
-			gchandle.get_intptr(), &SNAME("_notification"), args, 1, &call_error, &ret);
+	// Direct int dispatch — bypasses the Variant wrap+return-Variant alloc that the
+	// generic CSharpInstanceBridge_Call path requires for the single-int signature.
+	// Fires on every NOTIFICATION_PROCESS / PHYSICS_PROCESS / TRANSFORM_CHANGED for
+	// every C# script instance every frame, so the saved 2x Variant ctor/dtor matters.
+	GDMonoCache::managed_callbacks.CSharpInstanceBridge_CallNotification(
+			gchandle.get_intptr(), p_notification);
 }

 String CSharpInstance::to_string(bool *r_valid) {
--- a/modules/mono/glue/GodotSharp/GodotSharp/Core/Bridge/CSharpInstanceBridge.cs
+++ b/modules/mono/glue/GodotSharp/GodotSharp/Core/Bridge/CSharpInstanceBridge.cs
@@ -139,6 +139,26 @@ namespace Godot.Bridge
             }
         }

+        [UnmanagedCallersOnly]
+        internal static unsafe void CallNotification(IntPtr godotObjectGCHandle, int notification)
+        {
+            // Direct-int notification dispatch. Skips the Variant boxing/unboxing the
+            // generic Call path needs. _Notification(int) is the canonical user-overridable
+            // entry; the source-generated dispatcher routes NOTIFICATION_PROCESS etc.
+            // identically via this same virtual method.
+            try
+            {
+                var godotObject = (GodotObject)GCHandle.FromIntPtr(godotObjectGCHandle).Target;
+                if (godotObject == null)
+                    return;
+                godotObject._Notification(notification);
+            }
+            catch (Exception e)
+            {
+                ExceptionUtils.LogException(e);
+            }
+        }
+
         [UnmanagedCallersOnly]
         internal static void CallDispose(IntPtr godotObjectGCHandle, godot_bool okIfNull)
         {
